      • mergeMaps

        public static java.util.HashMap<java.lang.String,java.util.HashMap<java.lang.String,java.lang.Object>> mergeMaps(java.util.HashMap<java.lang.String,java.util.HashMap<java.lang.String,java.lang.Object>> primaryMap,
                                                                                                                 java.util.HashMap<java.lang.String,java.util.HashMap<java.lang.String,java.lang.Object>> secondaryMap,
                                                                                                                 java.lang.String keyAddition)
        Merges two maps by adding the secondaryMap to the primaryMap. To avoid issues where 2 map values have the same key, the secondaryMap has an additional value appended to its key.
        Parameters:
        primaryMap - the first map, it's value's keys are not changed
        secondaryMap - the second map, it's value's keys are changed
        keyAddition - the value to add to the second map's keys
        Returns:
        The merged maps

      • getIDFieldName

        public static java.lang.String getIDFieldName(java.util.List<java.lang.String> keys)
        Finds the ID field name from a list of keys. Keys are in format "tableName.fieldName" and the ID field name is in the format "tableNameID", so by iterating through all keys and finding one where the table name equals the field name - "ID", we find our ID field name. Keys are the keys for a hashmap found in Data.Data.
        Parameters:
        keys - list of map keys
        Returns:
        the IDFieldName, e.g. vaccineID
